ristine.website/blog/theres-a-node-2021-10-02</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/sejhtd/there_s_node_cluster_cloud"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 02 Oct 2021 12:19:48 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>PipeWire and fixing the Linux Video Capture stack</title><link>https://blogs.gnome.org/uraeus/2021/10/01/pipewire-and-fixing-the-linux-video-capture-stack/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/5k9waz/pipewire_fixing_linux_video_capture"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 01 Oct 2021 23:58:20 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>CosmicOS: a next-generation Contact message</title><link>https://cosmicos.github.io/about.html</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/q1d4do/cosmicos_next_generation_contact"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 02 Oct 2021 13:13:11 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>Qt's setContextProperty is a bad way to expose C++ classes to QML</title><link>https://raymii.org/s/articles/Qt_QML_Integrate_Cpp_with_QML_and_why_ContextProperties_are_bad.html</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/8bsjkx/qt_s_setcontextproperty_is_bad_way_expose"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 02 Oct 2021 16:04:10 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>Responsive QML layout with scrollbars</title><link>https://raymii.org/s/articles/Responsive_Qml_layout_with_scrollbars.html</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/yjku6h/responsive_qml_layout_with_scrollbars"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 02 Oct 2021 06:56:01 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>Dark mode</title><link>https://lobste.rs/s/eg1n75/dark_mode</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Hi folks,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lobsters now respects your UI’s dark mode setting. Typically your browser &lt;a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@media/prefers-color-scheme" rel="ugc"&gt;chooses&lt;/a&gt; based on your OS/GUI layer (&lt;a href="https://extensions.gnome.org/extension/2236/night-theme-switcher/" rel="ugc"&gt;Gnome&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/macos/visual-design/dark-mode/" rel="ugc"&gt;MacOS&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://developer.android.com/guide/topics/ui/look-and-feel/darktheme" rel="ugc"&gt;Android&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT210332" rel="ugc"&gt;IOS&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://blogs.windows.com/windowsexperience/2019/04/01/windows-10-tip-dark-theme-in-file-explorer/" rel="ugc"&gt;Windows&lt;/a&gt;), but maybe your browser overrides it (&lt;a href="https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/questions/1271928" rel="ugc"&gt;Firefox&lt;/a&gt;, apparently not Chrome?).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This &lt;a href="https://github.com/lobsters/lobsters/pull/1026/" rel="ugc"&gt;PR&lt;/a&gt; was substantial work by &lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/u/kevinc" rel="ugc"&gt;@kevinc&lt;/a&gt;. They did some great research on colorschemes and contrast guidelines. (They also &lt;a href="https://github.com/lobsters/lobsters/pull/1020" rel="ugc"&gt;caught&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://github.com/lobsters/lobsters/pull/1023" rel="ugc"&gt;dead&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://github.com/lobsters/lobsters/pull/1025" rel="ugc"&gt;code&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://github.com/lobsters/lobsters/pull/1021" rel="ugc"&gt;small&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://github.com/lobsters/lobsters/pull/1025" rel="ugc"&gt;improvements&lt;/a&gt; along the way!) Thanks for all your help, Kevin.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I figured it was worth an &lt;code&gt;announce&lt;/code&gt; post because everybody loves bikeshedding UI changes, as demonstrated on a &lt;a href="https://github.com/lobsters/lobsters/pull/823" rel="ugc"&gt;previous attempt&lt;/a&gt;. If you have an opinion about tweaking the dark mode, please post a comment in this thread rather than on one of the PRs or issues. It keeps the discussion visible, where otherwise I’m probably the only person who’d see every note deep on a particular line of a closed PR.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Best wishes and easy reading,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Peter&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 29 Sep 2021 13:08:09 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>Ice Lake Store Elimination</title><link>https://travisdowns.github.io/blog/2020/05/18/icelake-zero-opt.html</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/jbjdiu/ice_lake_store_elimination"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 01 Oct 2021 22:54:16 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>Zig, Skia, Clojure, Geometry and the Japanese TV Show: ICFP Contest 2021</title><link>https://tonsky.me/blog/icfpc-2021/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/ogwocq/zig_skia_clojure_geometry_japanese_tv"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 01 Oct 2021 07:40:33 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>The peasants are revolting</title><link>https://quuxplusone.github.io/blog/2021/09/30/the-peasants-are-revolting/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/gxhfow/peasants_are_revolting"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 02 Oct 2021 00:08:43 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>Analyzing the Mario Themed Malware</title><link>https://serhack.me/articles/analyzing-mario-malware-en/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/3o6bpn/analyzing_mario_themed_malware"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 01 Oct 2021 04:48:01 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>YAML 1.2.2 spec released</title><link>https://yaml.com/blog/2021-10/new-yaml-spec/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/66jpp6/yaml_1_2_2_spec_released"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 01 Oct 2021 11:35:58 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>Building a 10BASE5 “Thick Ethernet” network (2012)</title><link>http://www.mattmillman.com/projects/10base5/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/dfsxkn/building_10base5_thick_ethernet_network"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 01 Oct 2021 15:34:53 -0500</pubDate></it